# Voice Agent X-Ray — example environment file.
#
# Copy to `.env` and fill in. `.env` is gitignored and MUST NEVER be COPYied
# into the Docker image — secrets enter at `docker run` time only.
# See .claude/rules/public-repo.md §2.

# --- Server ---
# Port the Hono proxy listens on inside the container.
PORT=8080
# Bind address. 0.0.0.0 inside Docker; 127.0.0.1 if running bun directly on the host.
HOST=0.0.0.0
# Directory holding the SQLite store file (`xray.db`). In Docker this is the
# mounted volume; locally with `bun src/server/main.ts` set it to `./data`.
XRAY_DATA_DIR=/data

# --- Dev compose ---
# Run dev containers as the host user so files written into the bind-mounted
# repo (./:/app) are owned by you, not root. Without these, a compromised dev
# dependency could write to .git/hooks, package.json, etc. with root perms.
# Export from your shell or set them here — Docker Compose substitutes both:
#   export UID GID                 # bash/zsh
UID=1000
GID=1000

# --- Provider API keys (set the one(s) you actually use) ---
# ElevenLabs (Agent Workflows). Get one at https://elevenlabs.io/app/settings/api-keys
# ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=

# --- Agent replay test webhook (xray contributors only) ---
# These are used ONLY by scripts/agent-webhook.ts, which is a throwaway test
# server that contributors hacking on this repo bring up via `pnpm dev:webhook`
# to verify the replay loop end-to-end. Not part of the shipped image and not
# something xray users ever need to set — they have their own agent loop.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# AGENT_SYSTEM_PROMPT=You are a helpful voice agent. Reply in one or two short sentences.
